description.narrative: National capacity in planning and implementing health, nutrition and WASH services has improved, resulting in: a national scale up of EENC in 96 per cent of health facilities, benefiting 802,000 new-borns; integrated immunization sessions organized in hard-to-reach communes; strong government commitment for stunting reduction and sustainable financing for WASH; retention of the mandatory regulation on food fortification for control of iodine and other micronutrient deficiencies; and strengthened partnership and coordination for nutrition and WASH. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
